OL,3,CHit-and-run victim makes appeal from
OL,4,Chospital bed
OL,6,FThe victim of a hit-and-run incident
OL,7,Fin Portsmouth has appealed for
OL,8,Fwitnesses from her hospital bed. Liz
OL,9,FPullen will have a further operation
OL,10,Ftomorrow, having broken bones in her
OL,11,Fleg, knee and ankle. She sustained the
OL,12,Finjuries in a collision between her
OL,13,Fmoped and a white van.
OL,15,FShe told ITV Meridian she faces months
OL,16,Fof rehabilitaiton and worries she may
OL,17,Fnever fully recover. Liz was on her
OL,18,Fmoped in Burfields Road in Portsmouth
OL,19,Fon Friday 23rd January. The driver of
OL,20,Fthe white van didn't stop.
